-- Australian Wheat Crop Forecast at 22.3 Million Tons, National Bank Says
-- Wendy Pugh
-- 2010-07-26T22:34:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/australian-wheat-crop-forecast-at-22-3-million-tons-national-bank-says.html

          
          
             Wheat production in Australia may be
22.3 million metric tons in 2010-11 as improved soil moisture in
eastern states assists yields, National Australia Bank Ltd.
forecast in an e-mailed report today. That compared with its
June forecast for a crop of 22.2 million tons.  
 Risks to the projection included outbreaks of locusts and
mice in southern and eastern Australia and continued dry
conditions in Western Australia, the bank said.  
